Implement undo commands for the track/clip operations in a DAW project.

## Context

This is a TypeScript/React DAW project using Zustand for state management.

The UndoCommand interface is at `/Users/Nathan/Documents/Code/long-running-harness/src/state/undo/undo-command.ts`:
```typescript
export type UndoCommand = {
  readonly type: string;
  execute(): void;
  undo(): void;
  serialize(): Record<string, unknown>;
};
```

The UndoManager is at `/Users/Nathan/Documents/Code/long-running-harness/src/state/undo/undo-manager.ts` and uses push/undo/redo.

The DawStore at `/Users/Nathan/Documents/Code/long-running-harness/src/state/store.ts` has these track/clip actions:
- addTrack(track, index?)
- removeTrack(id)
- updateTrack(id, patch)
- reorderTrack(id, toIndex)
- addClip(clip)
- removeClip(id)
- moveClip(id, startTime, toTrackId?)
- splitClip(id, atTime) -> newId
- trimClip(id, newStart?, newEnd?)
- duplicateClip(id) -> newId

The track/clip types are at `/Users/Nathan/Documents/Code/long-running-harness/src/state/track/types.ts`:
```typescript
export type TrackModel = {
  readonly id: string;
  readonly name: string;
  readonly type: TrackType;
  readonly color: string;
  readonly muted: boolean;
  readonly solo: boolean;
  readonly armed: boolean;
  readonly volume: number;
  readonly pan: number;
  readonly clipIds: readonly string[];
};

export type ClipModel = {
  readonly id: string;
  readonly trackId: string;
  readonly sourceId: string;
  readonly startTime: number;
  readonly sourceOffset: number;
  readonly duration: number;
  readonly gain: number;
  readonly fadeIn: number;
  readonly fadeOut: number;
  readonly name: string;
};
```

## Task

1. Write tests FIRST at `/Users/Nathan/Documents/Code/long-running-harness/src/state/track/track-commands.test.ts`
2. Then implement at `/Users/Nathan/Documents/Code/long-running-harness/src/state/track/track-commands.ts`
3. Export from `/Users/Nathan/Documents/Code/long-running-harness/src/state/track/index.ts`

## Requirements

Create UndoCommand implementations for these operations:
- AddTrackCommand / RemoveTrackCommand (add track ↔ remove track)
- AddClipCommand / RemoveClipCommand
- MoveClipCommand (stores old startTime and trackId)
- SplitClipCommand (stores the two resulting clip ids and data so it can rejoin on undo)
- TrimClipCommand (stores old clip state)
- DuplicateClipCommand (stores the new clip id to remove on undo)
- UpdateTrackCommand (stores old and new patch values)
- ReorderTrackCommand (stores from/to indices)

Each command:
- Has a `type` string (e.g., "add-track")
- `execute()` calls the store action
- `undo()` reverses it
- `serialize()` returns data needed for deserialization

## Rules

- Use path aliases: `@state/store`, `@state/track/types`
- NO non-null assertions (`!`). Use safe access patterns.
- NO `delete` on dynamic properties. Use Object.fromEntries/filter.
- Format with prettier: `npx prettier --write <file>`
- Run tests: `pnpm test -- src/state/track/track-commands.test.ts`
- Run full suite at end: `pnpm test`
- TypeScript strict mode is ON with `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` and `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`

